{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}
{{unreferenced|date=July 2009}}

The '''1954 Sydney to Hobart Yacht Race''' was won on handicap by ''Solveig'', making her the overall winner in 1954. She had obtained [[line honours]] in 1953. The 36-foot double ender that was built in 1950 in Sydney by the Norwegian boatyard, [[Halvorsen & Sons]], was fabricated of Huon Pine, a rare wood, the second-oldest organism known to mankind, and found only in the rain-forests of [[Tasmania]]. ''Solveig'' is still a sound vessel, lying off [[Honolulu, Hawaii]], U.S.A.

