'''Cejhae Colin Greene''' (born 6 October 1995) is an [[Antigua and Barbuda|Antiguan]] [[Sprint (running)|sprinter]]. He attended the [[Princess Margaret School]].<ref>[http://trackfield97.com/cejhae-greene-%E2%80%93-antigua-barbuda-u20-sprint-hopeful/ Cejhae Greene – Antigua & Barbuda U20 sprint hopeful]. Trackfield97.com. Retrieved on 2016-08-14.</ref> Cejhae is the first of three children born to Jonah Greene and Colin Greene.<ref>[https://antiguaobserver.com/greene-to-shine-in-florida-state/ Greene To Shine In Florida State]. ''Antigua Observer'' (2014-01-08). Retrieved 2018-05-22.</ref>

Greene won a bronze medal in the 100 metres at the [[2012 Central American and Caribbean Junior Championships in Athletics]] in [[San Salvador]], [[El Salvador]].<ref>[http://www.antiguanice.com/v2/client.php?id=1020&news=4317 Greene Medals at XIX CAC Junior Games]. Antiguanice.com. Retrieved on 2016-08-14.</ref>

