{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Sport & Social Issues | cover = Journal of Sport & Social Issues.tif | editor = C. L. Cole | discipline = | former_names = | abbreviation = J. Sport Soc. Issues | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1977 -present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.093 | impact-year = 2017 | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal200897?siteId=sage-us&prodTypes=any&q=Journal+of+Sport+and+Social+Issues&fs=1 | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://jss.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 0193-7235 | eISSN = | OCLC = 731011150 | LCCN = 79643459 }}
'''''The Journal of Sport & Social Issues''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes papers in the field of [[sociology]]. The journal's [[Editor-in-Chief|editor]] is C. L. Cole ([[University of Illinois]]). It has been in publication since 1977 and is currently published by [[SAGE Publications]].
== Scope == ''The Journal of Sport & Social Issues'' publishes research, discussion and analysis on contemporary sport issues. The journal is of an international, interdisciplinary perspective and aims to examine pressing, topical questions about sport. ''The Journal of Sport & Social Issues'' studies the impact of sport on in areas such as psychology, cultural studies and anthropology.
== Abstracting and indexing == ''The Journal of Sport & Social Issues'' is abstracted and indexed in, among other databases: [[SCOPUS]], and the [[Social Sciences Citation Index]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', its 2017 [[impact factor]] is 1.093, ranking it 78 out of 146 journals in the category ‘Sociology’.<ref name=WoS>{{cite web |url=https://jcr.incites.thomsonreuters.com/JCRJournalProfileAction.action?pg=JRNLPROF&year=2015&journalTitle=JOURNAL OF SPORT & SOCIAL ISSUES&journal=J SPORT SOC ISSUES&edition=SSCI |year=2017 |title=Journals Ranked by Impact: Sociology |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] 2017 Journal Citation Reports |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2017-03-26}}</ref> and 40 out of 50 journals in the category ‘Hospitality, Leisure, Sport & Tourism’.<ref name=WoS1>{{cite web |url=https://jcr.incites.thomsonreuters.com/JCRJournalHomeAction.action?pg=JRNLHOME&year=2015&edition=SSCI&categories=MW |year=2017 |title=Journals Ranked by Impact: Hospitality, Leisure, Sport & Tourism |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] 2017 Journal Citation Reports |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2017-03-26}}</ref>
