{{Infobox Venue | name = Complejo Deportivo La Gamboína | image = | image_caption = | nickname = La Gamboína | location = [[Rancagua]], [[Chile]] | coordinates = {{coord|34|9|21|S|70|41|44|W|display=inline,title|type:landmark}} | type = Sports facility | opened = | closed = | owner = [[O'Higgins F.C.]] | construction_cost= | former_names = | website = http://www.ohigginsfc.cl/ }}
'''La Gamboína''' is the [[O'Higgins F.C.]] training facilities located in [[Rancagua]], [[Chile]]. It was replaced for the first-team by the [[Monasterio Celeste]], which since 2014 is the training ground of the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ohigginsfc.cl/el-club/|title=O'Higgins F.C. official website|accessdate=March 2, 2014}}</ref>
The complex consists of five pitches of natural grass, located in the north-east of the city. After the announce of the construction of the new complex, only the first-team abandoned in the 2013, but today the youth teams follow playing in the complex.
