The '''New Zealand Racing Hall of Fame''' recognises and honours those whose achievements have enriched the [[New Zealand]] [[thoroughbred horse racing]] industry. The [[Hall of Fame]]'s first group of honorees were inducted in 2006,<ref>{{cite news |title=Asian Racing Conference - Latest |url=https://www.sportingpost.co.za/2014/05/asian-racing-conference-latest/ |accessdate=2018-06-16 |work=Sporting Post |date=6 May 2014}}</ref> and inductions are held every other year.<ref name="NZR fell 2018">{{cite web |title=Fell proud of New Zealand Racing Hall Of Fame |url=https://www.nzracing.co.nz/News/23838/Fell-proud-of-New-Zealand-Racing-Hall-Of-Fame.aspx |publisher=NZRacing |accessdate=2018-06-16 |language=en |date=7 February 2018}}</ref> The inaugural chairman was Gerald Fell.<ref name="NZR fell 2018"/>
